  "short_description": "5GHz 802.11ac, 720MHz CPU, 128MB RAM, 5x GLAN ports, RouterOS L4",
  "description": "The MikroTik OmniTIK 5 ac, bearing the manufacture part number RBOmniTikG-5HacD, is a robust outdoor wireless access point designed for high-performance networking in challenging environments. This device features a MIPSBE architecture and is powered by a QCA9557 CPU running at a nominal frequency of 720 MHz.",
  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "OmniTIK 5 ac Series",
      "text": "The MikroTik OmniTIK 5 ac, bearing the manufacture part number RBOmniTikG-5HacD, is a robust outdoor wireless access point designed for high-performance networking in challenging environments. This device features a MIPSBE architecture and is powered by a QCA9557 CPU running at a nominal frequency of 720 MHz. It operates on MikroTik's reliable RouterOS with a Level 4 license, providing a comprehensive suite of networking capabilities and comes with a new design weatherproof outdoor enclosure, two integrated 7.5dBi 5GHz omni antennas, a power supply, a PoE injector and a mounting kit."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "text": "The OmniTIK 5 ac includes 128 MB of RAM and 16 MB of FLASH storage, ensuring ample space for configurations and stable operation. The device's dimensions are 416 x 129 x 58 mm, making it a compact yet powerful addition to any network setup. It is designed to withstand extreme temperatures, with a tested ambient temperature range of -40°C to 70°C and boasts an impressive MTBF of approximately 200,000 hours at 25°C, ensuring long-term reliability."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "text": "This model includes a single DC input for PoE-IN, supporting a voltage range of 12-57 V, and has a maximum power consumption of 14 W. The passive cooling system ensures that the device operates silently and efficiently without the need for mechanical cooling components. The PoE in feature supports Passive PoE, providing flexibility in power options."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "text": "In terms of wired connectivity, the OmniTIK 5 ac provides five 10/100/1000 Ethernet ports, facilitating high-speed wired connections for multiple devices. It also includes one USB port with USB Power Reset capability and a USB type A slot, enhancing its versatility for various networking applications. The wireless capabilities of the OmniTIK 5 ac are noteworthy, with a maximum data rate of 867 Mbit/s on the 5 GHz band. It supports 802.11a/n/ac standards and features 2 chains for enhanced signal reliability and performance. The device is equipped with a QCA9892 wireless chip and offers an antenna gain of 7.5 dBi, leveraging Wi-Fi 5 technology to ensure robust and efficient wireless communication."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "text": "Overall, the MikroTik OmniTIK 5 ac is a powerful and reliable solution for outdoor wireless networking, offering high-speed connectivity, durability, and extensive features to support complex networking needs. Its combination of robust specifications and advanced technology makes it an excellent choice for expanding and enhancing wireless network infrastructure. The OmniTIK 5 ac is built to meet rigorous international standards, holding certifications from CE, FCC, IC, EAC, and ROHS. Its IP54 rating ensures protection against dust and water splashes, making it suitable for outdoor installations in diverse environments."
    }
  ],
